es can be served warm or cold with <em>Custard<\/em> and fresh fruit. Transfer any leftovers into a sealable container and store in the refrigerator to enjoy the next day.","Use any leftover ricotta in the <em>Pancetta pine nut and ricotta pappardelle<\/em> or <em>Spinach and ricotta patties in tomato sauce<\/em>.","Visit the official Thermomix Recipe Community (recipecommunity.com.au) to learn how to make ricotta in the Thermomix."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","55m","4 portions"]}